work.work-title: O Love of God, How Strong and True

credit.credit-words: O Love of God, How Strong and True
Text: Horatius Bomar, 1861 Tune: William Knapp, 1738

6 We read your power to bless and save e'en in the darkness of the grave; still more in resurrection light we read the fullness of your might.
7 O love of God, our shield and stay through all the perils of our way; eternal love, in you we rest, forever safe, forever blest.
